<h2 id="Introducci%C3%B3n-a-la-mec%C3%A1nica-de-fluidos,-parte-1">Introducci&#243;n a la mec&#225;nica de fluidos, parte 1<a class="anchor-link" href="#Introducci%C3%B3n-a-la-mec%C3%A1nica-de-fluidos,-parte-1"></a></h2><p>La aerodinámica es la rama de la física que estudia el comportamiento del aire y otros gases en movimiento, y cómo estos interactúan con los objetos sólidos. El objetivo de este notebook es proporcionar la teoría que sustenta el campo y, gracias a la superposición, poder ser usada como bloques de construcción en simulaciones básicas.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="input">
<div class="inner_cell">

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Desde la clásica ecuación de continuidad, podemos establecer un principio básico: la &quot;ley de conservación de masa&quot;; es decir, que no se modifique la cantidad de masa en el proceso de interacción del campo de velocidades $\vec{v}$. En otras palabras, la tasa de cambio de masa dentro del volumen es igual a la masa que entra menos la masa que sale. Gracias a la ayuda del cálculo vectorial, podemos expresar la idea anterior de la siguiente forma:</p>
$$ 
\frac{\partial \rho}{\partial t} + \vec{\nabla} \cdot (\rho \vec{v}) = 0 
$$<p>donde:</p>
<ol>
<li>$\rho$ es la densidad del fluido,</li>
<li>$\vec{v}$ es el campo de velocidades del fluido.</li>
</ol>
<p>Entonces, aquí es donde podemos asumir ciertas cosas. Por ejemplo, si asumimos que la densidad de la masa no cambiará en el tiempo (o sea, que no se gana ni pierde masa), estamos en presencia de un &quot;flujo incompresible&quot;, y la densidad de este flujo $\rho$ será constante en el tiempo, por lo que:</p>
$$
\frac{\partial \rho}{\partial t} = 0
$$<p>Dado que $\rho$ también es una constante espacial, la ecuación de continuidad nos arroja un resultado importantísimo:</p>
$$
\vec{\nabla} \cdot \vec{v} = 0,
$$<p>Esta es la forma más simple de la ecuación de continuidad para un flujo incompresible. Dicho todo lo anterior, la Aerodinámica asume que la masa del aire se conserva en cualquier volumen de control considerado, por ende, el <em>campo de velocidades</em> $\vec{v}(\vec{r})$ describe la velocidad del aire en cada punto del espacio y en cada instante de tiempo.</p>
<p>Por supuesto, el hecho que $\vec{\nabla} \cdot \vec{v}(\vec{r}) = 0$ significa que existe un <em>flujo potencial</em> $\phi(\vec{r})$ tal que:</p>
$$
\vec{v} = -\vec{\nabla} \phi(\vec{r}),
$$<p>Por lo que llegamos a la ecuación de Laplace:</p>
$$
\nabla^2 \phi(\vec{r}) = 0,
$$<p>en otras palabras, cualquier solución a la ecuación de Laplace es, a su vez, un <em>flujo potencial aerodinámico</em>. Como la ecuación de Laplace es lineal y homogénea, significa que el principio de superposición es válido, por lo que si $\phi_1$ y $\phi_2$ son soluciones de la ecuación de Laplace, entonces cualquier combinación lineal:</p>
$$
\phi_3 = C_1 \phi_1 + C_2 \phi_2
$$<p>también es una solución, donde $C1$ y $C2$ son constantes.</p>
<p>Si partimos desde estas bases podemos considerar cierta fenomenología física y darle significado en dos dimensiones.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Soluciones-irrotacionales:-Fuentes,-sumideros">Soluciones irrotacionales: Fuentes, sumideros<a class="anchor-link" href="#Soluciones-irrotacionales:-Fuentes,-sumideros"></a></h3><p>Hasta ahora solo hablamos sobre las propiedades del campo de velocidades que hemos de representar. Para poder describir las propiedades del campo de velocidades vectoriales $\vec{v}$, podemos recurrir al concepto de &quot;circulación&quot; dentro del campo, es decir, a la integral de línea sobre un contorno $C$ cerrado del campo de velocidades, es decir:</p>
$$
\Gamma = \oint_C \vec{v} \cdot d\vec{r},
$$<p>Al considerar que la curva cerrada $C$ es la frontera de una superficie $S$, podemos aplicar el teorema de Stokes de la siguiente forma:</p>
$$
{\displaystyle \oint_{\partial S} \vec{v} \cdot d\vec{r} =\iint_S \left(\nabla \times \vec {v} \right)\cdot \hat{n}dS },
$$<p>donde $\partial S$ es la curva que recorre el borde de la superficie $S$ orientada en la dirección normal a la superficie $\hat{n}$. En otras palabras: La circulación en una curva cerrada es igual a la integral sobre la superficie orientada S del rotacional de la velocidad, o <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vorticity"><em>Vorticidad</em></a> $\vec{\omega} = \vec{\nabla} \times \vec{v}$. Al considerar un campo <em>irrotacional</em> La vorticidad $\vec{\omega} = \vec{\nabla} \times \vec{v} = \vec{0}$.</p>
<p>Como para un fluido incompresible se tiene que que:</p>
$$
\nabla \times \vec {v} = \nabla \times (-\vec{\nabla} \phi) = \vec{0} 
$$<p>Por lo que estamos ante la presencia de un <em>flujo irrotacional</em>, una propiedad de los campos vectoriales conservativos que pueden ser descritos en términos de un campo escalar potencial $\phi(\vec{r})$.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="La-Funci%C3%B3n-fuente">La Funci&#243;n fuente<a class="anchor-link" href="#La-Funci%C3%B3n-fuente"></a></h3><p>Por ejemplo está el <em>Flujo fuente</em> o solamente <em>fuente</em>, el cual es un punto  en el espacio desde donde proviene un fluido de forma continua, por lo tanto, líneas radiales del campo de velocidades son emanadas desde ese punto, y su magnitud decrece con la distancia.</p>
<p>Es un caso análogo al electromagnetismo, donde uno puede asignar a las cargas eléctricas las &quot;fuentes de campo eléctrico&quot;. Por lo tanto, al asumir una <em>superficie Gaussiana</em> $S$ y usando el teorema de la divergecia en esta fuente, podríamos obtener la tasa de flujo volumétrico, sin embargo este planteamiento es en 2D, por lo que vamos a calcular el flujo del campo de velocidades a través de un segmento de la curva $C$.</p>
<p>Por ejemplo, si pensamos en un objeto puntual donde sólo radían lineas de campo hacia el espacio de forma radial, de tal forma que $\vec{v}=v_r\hat{r}$, podríamos elegir una trayectoria arbitraria $C$ tal que rodeara esta <em>fuente</em>, y así lograr obtener una expresión para su campo de velocidades $v_r$.</p>
$$
\sigma = \oint_{\text{C}} \vec{v} \cdot \hat{n} dr
$$<p>Si consideramos una &quot;trayectoria Amperiana&quot;, de forma que un círculo de radio $R$ rodee esta fuente de campo. Un vector posición paramétrico a la variable $\theta$ dentro de [0,2$\pi$] describe la situación a la perfección:</p>
$$
\vec{r}(\theta) = Rcos(\theta)\hat{i}+Rsen(\theta)\hat{j}, 
$$<p>al diferenciarlo, tenemos que el radio de la esfera R es constante, sólo la variable paramétrica $\theta$ varía. Así:</p>
$$
\begin{aligned}
d\vec{r}(\theta) &amp;= \frac{d \vec{r}}{d\theta} d\theta  \\
            &amp;= \frac{d}{d\theta}\left( Rcos(\theta)\hat{i}+Rsen(\theta)\hat{j} \right) d\theta  \\
            &amp;= R\left( -sen(\theta)\hat{i}+cos(\theta)\hat{j} \right) d\theta  \\
            &amp;= R  d\theta \hat{\theta} \\
\end{aligned}
$$<p>donde la dirección $\hat{\theta}$ de diferenciación en este caso es en el sentido donde se mueve la parametrización para describirse completamente. Por lo tanto usaremos el valor $|d\vec{r}| = Rd\theta$. En todo punto la trayectoria $C$ es circular, por lo que la dirección normal a la superficie es $\hat{n}=\hat{r}$, y el valor de la velocidad radial $v_r$ es constante en cada punto de la curva. El flujo neto o <em>fuerza de la fuente</em> $\sigma$ puede ser descrita por:</p>
$$
\begin{aligned}
\sigma &amp;= \oint_{\text{C}} \vec{v} \cdot \hat{n} dr \\
       &amp;= \oint_{\text{C}} v_r\hat{r} \cdot \hat{r} R d\theta \\
       &amp;= v_r R \oint_{\text{C}} d\theta \\
       &amp;= v_r R 2 \pi \\
\end{aligned}
$$<p>donde la integral de camino $\oint_{\text{C}} d\theta = 2\pi$ es un camino completo a través de un círculo de radio $R$ arbitrario, pero fijo. Por lo tanto, la fuerza de la fuente será un parámetro que caracteriza la cantidad o la fuerza (valga la redudancia) que esta fuente emite lineas de campo. Como es un parámetro escalar, en realidad estamos buscando una expresión para la el campo de velocidades radiales, es decir:</p>
$$
\sigma = 2 \pi r  v_r,
$$<p>Lo que podemos escribir de forma más conveniente de la forma:</p>
$$
v_r = \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}.
$$<p>La fuerza de la fuente $\sigma$ es un parámetro importante, dado que si es positivo, líneas de campo saldrán desde la fuente, si $\sigma$ es negativo, ya no será más una fuente, sino que una receptora de lineas de campo: <em>Un sumidero</em>, por no decir un &quot;desagüe&quot;</p>
<p>Así, podemos describir la función fuente de un campo de velocidades es:</p>
$$
\begin{aligned}
\vec{v} &amp;= v_r\hat{r} + v_\theta\hat{\theta}  \\
        &amp;= \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}\hat{r} + 0\hat{\theta}\\
        &amp;= \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}\hat{r} \\
\end{aligned}
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>En coordenadas cilíndricas (que asumimos al aplicar la simetria radial) podemos describir la distancia a cualquier punto usando $r = \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}$, por lo tanto el vector unitario $\hat{r}=\cos(\theta)\hat{i} + \sin(\theta)\hat{j}$, es decir:</p>
$$
\begin{aligned}
\vec{v} &amp;= \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}\hat{r}  \\
        &amp;= \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} \left( \cos(\theta)\hat{i} + \sin(\theta)\hat{j} \right) \\
        &amp;= \left( \frac{\sigma \cos(\theta)}{2 \pi \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} \right)\hat{i}+ \left( \frac{\sigma \sin(\theta)}{2 \pi \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} \right)\hat{j}\\
        &amp;= \left( \frac{\sigma r \cos(\theta)}{2 \pi (x^2 + y^2)} \right)\hat{i}+ \left( \frac{\sigma r \sin(\theta)}{2 \pi (x^2 + y^2)} \right)\hat{j}\\
        &amp;= \left( \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi} \frac{x}{(x^2 + y^2)} \right)\hat{i}+ \left( \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi} \frac{y}{(x^2 + y^2)} \right)\hat{j},\\
\end{aligned}
$$<p>Así, tenemos que $\vec{v}(x,y)= v_x \hat{i} + v_y \hat{j}$, es decir:</p>
$$
v_x = \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi} \frac{x}{(x^2 + y^2)}
$$$$
v_y = \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi} \frac{y}{(x^2 + y^2)}
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="inner_cell">

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Así todo el flujo sale desde la fuente. Veamos que la dirección del flujo depende de la fuerza de la fuente $\sigma$, dado que al ser positivo es fuente, y al ser negativo es un <em>sumidero</em>, o un lugar que recibe líneas de velocidad de forma radial, en analogía a la carga magnética positiva y negativa $q$, existe la fuente y el sumidero dado el signo de $\sigma$.</p>
<p>Como la superposición también es válida, el siguiente plot mostrará el campo de velocidades de la suma de una fuente más un sumidero, es decir:</p>
$$
\vec{v}_{\mbox{total}} = \sum_{i=1}^2 \vec{v}_i = \vec{v}_{\mbox{fuente}} + \vec{v}_{\mbox{sumidero}}.
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">nx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ny</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">100</span>
<span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">nx</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ny</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">meshgrid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">fuerza_fuente</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">15.0</span>

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Como tenemos que $\vec{v} = - \vec{\nabla} \phi(\vec{r})$, podemos obtener una expresión para el potencial escalar $\phi(r,\theta)$ el cual es una funcion escalar en coordenadas polares. Para esto, debemos recordar cómo se define el gradiente $\vec{\nabla}$ en coordenadas polares:</p>
$$
\nabla \phi = \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial r} \hat{r} + \frac{1}{r} \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial \theta} \hat{\theta},
$$<p>Por lo tanto:</p>
$$
\vec{v}(r,\theta) = - \nabla \phi = - \left( \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial r} \hat{r} + \frac{1}{r} \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial \theta} \hat{\theta}\right),
$$<p>entonces, podemos igualar componente, teniendo que:</p>
<ol>
<li>Componente angul</li>
</ol>
<p>ar $\theta$. Como es nula, se concluye que el potencial $\phi$ no depende de $\theta$, es decir:</p>
$$
0 = -\frac{1}{r}\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial \theta}.
$$$$
\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial \theta} = 0 \Rightarrow \phi = \phi(r) 
$$<ol start="2">
<li>Componente radial $r$.</li>
</ol>
$$
\frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}\hat{r} =  -\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial r} \hat{r}
$$$$
\frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r} = -\frac{\partial \phi}{\partial r} \Rightarrow \partial \phi = -\frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}{\partial r} 
$$<p>Integrando por ambos lados:</p>
$$
\int \partial \phi = -\int \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}{\partial r} 
$$$$
\phi(r) = -\frac{\sigma}{2 \pi} \ln(r) + C 
$$<p>Por lo tanto, otra forma de expresar el campo de velocidades $\vec{v}$ es a través del gradiente del campo escalar $\phi(r)$:</p>
$$
\vec{v} = - \vec{\nabla} \phi(\vec{r})  = - \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial r} \hat{r} = \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi}\frac{\partial \ln(r)}{\partial r} \hat{r}
$$$$
\Rightarrow \vec{v} = \frac{\sigma}{2 \pi r}\hat{r}.
$$<p>Todo consistente.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Un-v%C3%B3rtice">Un v&#243;rtice<a class="anchor-link" href="#Un-v%C3%B3rtice"></a></h3><p>Un vórtice es un movimiento de fluido en líneas de corriente circulares. Imagina líneas de corriente que son círculos concéntricos alrededor de un punto dado. Sin embargo, esto no significa que los elementos del fluido estén rotando sobre sí mismos.</p>
<p>En un vórtice irrotacional, la velocidad tangencial $v_\theta$ es constante a lo largo de una línea de corriente circular y es inversamente proporcional al radio $r$, y la velocidad radial $v_r=0$, por lo tanto:</p>
$$
\vec{v} = v_r \hat{r} + v_\theta \hat{\theta} = \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi r} \hat{\theta}.
$$<p>Así, la vorticidad $\omega = \vec{\nabla} \times \vec{v}$ es cero en todas partes, excepto en la ubicación del punto vórtice, donde la derivada de la velocidad es infinita. Entonces, como $\hat{\theta} = (-sen(\theta)\hat{i}+cos(\theta)\hat{j})$, tenemos que:</p>
$$
\begin{aligned}
\vec{v} &amp;= \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi r} \hat{\theta}  \\
        &amp;= \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} \left(-\sin(\theta)\hat{i}+\cos(\theta)\hat{j} \right) \\
        &amp;= -\left(\frac{\Gamma \sin(\theta)}{2 \pi \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} \right)\hat{i}+ \left( \frac{\Gamma \cos(\theta)}{2 \pi \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} \right)\hat{j}\\
        &amp;= -\left(\frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi} \frac{y}{x^2 + y^2} \right)\hat{i}+ \left( \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi}\frac{x} {(x^2 + y^2)} \right)\hat{j}\\
        \\
\end{aligned}
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>

            <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">posx_vortice</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">((</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">posx_vortice</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">posy_vortice</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">))</span>

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>De forma análoga a la anterior, podemos obtener la funcion escalar $\phi$ asociada:</p>
$$
\vec{v}(r,\theta) = - \nabla \phi = - \left( \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial r} \hat{r} + \frac{1}{r} \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial \theta} \hat{\theta}\right),
$$<p>Por lo tanto:</p>
$$
\frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi r} \hat{\theta} = - \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial \theta} \hat{\theta}
$$$$
\Rightarrow \phi(\theta) = - \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi r} \theta + Const
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Funci%C3%B3n-de-corriente-$%5Cpsi$">Funci&#243;n de corriente $\psi$<a class="anchor-link" href="#Funci%C3%B3n-de-corriente-$%5Cpsi$"></a></h3><p>La función de corriente $\psi$ es muy útil para describir las trayectorias de objetos dentro de las lineas de corriente sobre un campo de velocidades 2D de un flujo incompresible. Considerando un campo de velocidades $\vec{v}(r,\theta)$, la función de corriente $\psi(r,\theta)$ se define de la siguiente forma:</p>
$$
\begin{aligned}
\vec{v} &amp;= v_r\hat{r} + v_\theta \hat{\theta} \\
        &amp;= \frac{1}{r}\frac{\partial \psi}{\partial \theta}\hat{r} - \frac{\partial \psi}{\partial r} \hat{\theta}, \\
\end{aligned}
$$<p>aunque la definición es algo extraña, es una función asociada o relacionada al potencial escalar $\phi$ en la idea del reduccionismo de las expresiones para simplificar el calculo. Lo interesante es que las variables de la función son elegidas tal que deja intactas sus propiedades. Por ej. sobre la ecuación de continuidad para un flujo incompresible:</p>
$$
\begin{aligned}
\vec{\nabla} \cdot \vec{v} =&amp; \ 0, \\
\left( \frac{1}{r} \frac{\partial (r\ \ ) }{\partial r} \hat{r} + \frac{1}{r} \frac{\partial }{\partial \theta} \hat{\theta} \right) \cdot \left( v_r\hat{r} + v_\theta \hat{\theta} \right) =&amp; \ 0, \\
\left( \frac{1}{r} \frac{\partial (r v_r ) }{\partial r} + \frac{1}{r} \frac{\partial v_\theta}{\partial \theta} \right) =&amp; \ 0, \\
\frac{1}{r}\frac{\partial^2 \psi}{\partial r \partial \theta} - \frac{1}{r}\frac{\partial^2 \psi}{\partial \theta \partial r} =&amp; \ 0 
\end{aligned}
$$<p>Muy bien. Pensemos en el campo de velocidades del vórtice y calculemos la función de Corriente $\psi$:</p>
$$
\mbox{Como }\vec{v} = \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi r} \hat{\theta}, \mbox{  Y además } \vec{v} = - \frac{\partial \psi}{\partial r}\hat{\theta}
$$$$
\Rightarrow - \frac{\partial \psi}{\partial r} = \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi r}
$$<p>Y de forma directa:</p>
$$
\Rightarrow \psi(r) = - \frac{\Gamma}{2 \pi} \ln(r) + C
$$<p>Lo interesante es que la función de corriente mapea regiones equipotenciales, y coincide la dirección de las lineas de flujo usando la función streamplot de matplotlib. El siguiente gráfico ilustra el campo vectorial en cada punto alrededor del vórtice irrotacional.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Función para calcular la función de corriente de un vórtice</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">funcion_corriente_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fuerza</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">psi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">fuerza</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">r</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">psi</span>

<span class="c1"># Función para calcular el campo de velocidad </span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">campo_velocidades_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fuerza</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">fuerza</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fuerza</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span>

<span class="c1"># Parámetros </span>
<span class="n">N</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">30</span>  
<span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mf">1.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.5</span>
<span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mf">1.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.5</span>
<span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">meshgrid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Parámetros del vórtice</span>
<span class="n">gamma</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">328.0</span>  

<span class="c1"># Calcular la función de corriente y el campo de velocidad del vórtice</span>
<span class="n">psi_vortex</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">funcion_corriente_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gamma</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">campo_velocidades_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gamma</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="c1"># Dibujar las líneas de corriente</span>
<span class="n">contour</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">contour</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">psi_vortex</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">levels</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">colors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;y&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;$\vec</span><span class="si">{v}</span><span class="s1">(x,y)$&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Normalizar la magnitud de los vectores para escalar </span>
<span class="n">magnitude</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">u</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">u_normalized</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">magnitude</span>
<span class="n">v_normalized</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">magnitude</span>

<span class="c1"># Dibujar los vectores normalizados </span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">quiver</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">magnitude</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">cmap</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;cividis&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">scale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1500</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.015</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">headwidth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">5.</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">headlength</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">6.</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Mostrar la gráfica</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Din%C3%A1mica-y-superposici%C3%B3n:-Movimiento-de-Part%C3%ADculas">Din&#225;mica y superposici&#243;n: Movimiento de Part&#237;culas<a class="anchor-link" href="#Din%C3%A1mica-y-superposici%C3%B3n:-Movimiento-de-Part%C3%ADculas"></a></h3><p>Implementamos partículas para poder visualizar de mejor forma la dinamica de los sistemas antes descritos. Como para cada punto $(x,y)$ existe un campo de velocidades $\vec{v}(u,v)$, las partículas se moverán según el campo de velocidad total. Para cada partícula, se calcula su nueva posición utilizando las componentes $u$ y $v$ del campo de velocidad en su posición actual:</p>
$$
x_{\text{nueva}} = x_{\text{actual}} + u \cdot \Delta t
$$$$
y_{\text{nueva}} = y_{\text{actual}} + v \cdot \Delta t
$$<p>Es decir, usamos la ecuación itinerario para poder determinar la posición de cada partícula mientras evoluciona en el tiempo. En el código, $\Delta t$ es un factor pequeño (0.0167) que escala la velocidad a un tiempo &quot;real&quot;.</p>
<p>Pseudo codigo</p>
<ol>
<li>Se calcula el campo de velocidades provocado por el artefacto matemático</li>
<li>Usando los vectores de cada punto, se dibujan las líneas de corriente.</li>
<li>Se mueven las partículas según el campo de velocidad.</li>
<li>Se dibujan las partículas y el proceso se repite por el tiempo total</li>
</ol>
<p>Con esto, el siguiente codigo representa la dinámica del campo de velocidades de un vórtice irrotacional:</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">campo_velocidad_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Gamma</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">epsilon</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">1e-6</span>  <span class="c1"># Para evitar división por cero</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">epsilon</span>
    <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">Gamma</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Gamma</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span>

<span class="c1"># Parámetros de la simulación</span>
<span class="n">N</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">100</span>
<span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mf">5.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">5.5</span>
<span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mf">5.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">5.5</span>
<span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">meshgrid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Parámetros del vórtice</span>
<span class="n">gamma</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">32.0</span>

<span class="c1"># Parámetros temporales</span>
<span class="n">fps</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">40</span>
<span class="n">delta_t</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0567</span>  <span class="c1"># Paso temporal de la simulación</span>
<span class="n">frames_totales</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">200</span>  

<span class="c1"># Crear la figura y los ejes</span>
<span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="c1"># Crear partículas aleatorias</span>
<span class="n">num_particles</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">100</span>
<span class="n">particles_x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">uniform</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_particles</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">particles_y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">uniform</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_particles</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">colors</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">&#39;r&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">num_particles</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">colors</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;g&#39;</span>
<span class="n">colors</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;b&#39;</span>

<span class="c1"># Función de actualización para la animación</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">animate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">clear</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlim</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylim</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xticks</span><span class="p">([])</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_yticks</span><span class="p">([])</span>

    <span class="c1"># Actualizar el campo de velocidad    </span>
    <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">campo_velocidad_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gamma</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">streamplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">density</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.8</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linewidth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">arrowsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">1.1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">arrowstyle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;-&gt;&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="c1"># Mover partículas según el campo de velocidad</span>
    <span class="k">global</span> <span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">particles_y</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">j</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">)):</span>
        <span class="n">x_idx</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">clip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_end</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)),</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">y_idx</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">clip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">particles_y</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_end</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)),</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
        <span class="n">u_particle</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">y_idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_idx</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="n">v_particle</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">y_idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_idx</span><span class="p">]</span>
        
        <span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">u_particle</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">delta_t</span>
        <span class="n">particles_y</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">v_particle</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">delta_t</span>

    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">particles_y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">c</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">colors</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;$\vec</span><span class="si">{v}</span><span class="s1">(x,y)$&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;$</span><span class="si">{X}</span><span class="s1">$&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;$</span><span class="si">{Y}</span><span class="s1">$&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="c1"># Actualizar el contador de tiempo</span>
    <span class="n">tiempo</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">delta_t</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">text</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.95</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.95</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Tiempo: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">tiempo</span><span class="si">:</span><span class="s1">.1f</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1"> s&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">transform</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">transAxes</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;right&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">va</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;top&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;w&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">[]</span>

<span class="c1"># Crear la animación</span>
<span class="n">ani</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">animation</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">FuncAnimation</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">animate</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">frames</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">frames_totales</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">interval</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1000</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">fps</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">blit</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Mostrar la animación en el notebook</span>
<span class="n">HTML</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ani</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_html5_video</span><span class="p">())</span>

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Luego, hacemos una animación de la superposición entre un vórtice y un sumidero, haciendo un campo de velocidades total, suma de los otros dos:</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">campo_velocidad_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Gamma</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">epsilon</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">1e-6</span>  <span class="c1"># Para evitar división por cero</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">epsilon</span>
    <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">Gamma</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Gamma</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">campo_velocidad_sumidero</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fuerza</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">epsilon</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">1e-6</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">epsilon</span>
    <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">fuerza</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">fuerza</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span>
         
<span class="c1"># Parámetros de la simulación</span>
<span class="n">N</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">100</span>
<span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mf">5.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">5.5</span>
<span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mf">5.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">5.5</span>
<span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">meshgrid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Parámetros del vórtice y sumidero</span>
<span class="n">gamma</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">22.0</span>
<span class="n">sigma</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">5</span>

<span class="c1"># Parámetros temporales</span>
<span class="n">fps</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">30</span>
<span class="n">delta_t</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0567</span>  <span class="c1"># Paso temporal</span>
<span class="n">frames_totales</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">200</span>

<span class="c1">#Crear la figura y los ejes</span>
<span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="c1"># Crear partículas aleatorias</span>
<span class="n">num_particles</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">300</span>
<span class="n">particles_x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">uniform</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_particles</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">particles_y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">uniform</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_particles</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">colors</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">&#39;r&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">num_particles</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">colors</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;g&#39;</span>
<span class="n">colors</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;b&#39;</span>

<span class="c1"># Texto del contador de tiempo</span>
<span class="n">timer_text</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">text</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.95</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.95</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">transform</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">transAxes</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;right&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">va</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;top&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;w&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Función de actualización para la animación</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">animate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">clear</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlim</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_end</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylim</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_end</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xticks</span><span class="p">([])</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_yticks</span><span class="p">([])</span>

    <span class="c1"># Campo de velocidad total</span>
    <span class="n">u_v</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v_v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">campo_velocidad_vortex</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gamma</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">u_s</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v_s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">campo_velocidad_sumidero</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">sigma</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="c1">#superposicion</span>
    <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">u_v</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">u_s</span>
    <span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">v_v</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">v_s</span>

    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">streamplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">density</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.8</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linewidth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">arrowsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">1.1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">arrowstyle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;-&gt;&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="c1"># Mover partículas según el campo de velocidad</span>
    <span class="k">global</span> <span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">particles_y</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">j</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">)):</span>
        <span class="n">x_idx</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">clip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x_end</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">x_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)),</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">y_idx</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">clip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">particles_y</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_end</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">y_start</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)),</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">N</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="n">u_particle</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">y_idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_idx</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="n">v_particle</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">y_idx</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_idx</span><span class="p">]</span>

        <span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">u_particle</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">delta_t</span>
        <span class="n">particles_y</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">v_particle</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">delta_t</span>

    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">particles_x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">particles_y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">c</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">colors</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">tiempo</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">delta_t</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">text</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.95</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.95</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Tiempo: </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">tiempo</span><span class="si">:</span><span class="s1">.1f</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1"> s&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">transform</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">transAxes</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;right&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">va</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;top&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;w&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;$\vec</span><span class="si">{v}</span><span class="s1">(x,y)$&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;$</span><span class="si">{X}</span><span class="s1">$&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;$</span><span class="si">{Y}</span><span class="s1">$&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">[]</span>

<span class="c1"># Crear la animación</span>
<span class="n">ani</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">animation</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">FuncAnimation</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">animate</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">frames</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">frames_totales</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">interval</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1000</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">fps</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">blit</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Mostrar en el notebook</span>
<span class="n">HTML</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ani</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_html5_video</span><span class="p">())</span>
